related_questions.question: How long does it take to smoke a fish?
related_questions.snippet: Place the fish fillets, skin side down, on a well greased grill approximately 4 to 6 inches from smoking chips. Close hood on grill and open vent slightly to keep smoke and air circulating. Smoke fish approximately 1 hour at 150° to 175° or for 30 to 45 minutes at 200°.

related_questions.question: Is smoked fish healthy to eat?
related_questions.snippet: Smoked fish, including salmon and mackerel, are both high in Omega 3 fatty acids. These are highly beneficial to our heart health, helping to reduce inflammation, managing heart rhythm and lowering triglycerides in our blood fats. These compounds also work to reduce the build-up of plaque in the blood vessels.

buttons.title: How To Smoke Fish In A Smoker | Recipe | Char-Broil New Zealand
buttons.snippet: Preheat smoker and add wood chips to get things going. We suggest letting the wood chips preheat for about 45 mins. Add fish and let smoke for about 3 hours. Whether your fish is caught wild from a stream or plucked from the meat aisle, it's vital to smoke your fish until it has reached a safe internal temperature.

buttons.subtitle: How Long Does Smoked Fish Last?
buttons.title: How to Safely Store Your Smoked Fish
buttons.snippet: When properly refrigerated, most unopened smoked fish products can retain peak flavor for 7-10 days (unless otherwise marked). However, once opened, it's advisable to consume within 5 days for best taste and texture.

buttons.snippet: Smoking and cooking A typical fish-smoking cycle (see Figure 1) should bring the fish to over 160°F internal temperature within 6 to 8 hours (internal—not oven—temperature). If your smokehouse cannot provide 200 to 225°F oven tem- peratures, you'll have to cook the final product in your kitchen oven.
